network.param.modules.inventory

Class InventoryManager

  • java.lang.Object
    • network.param.AbstModuleManager
      • network.param.AbstUploadModuleManager
        • network.param.modules.inventory.InventoryManager
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IBulkImport, IInventoryManager

    public final class InventoryManager
extends AbstUploadModuleManager
implements IInventoryManager
    Implementation of IInventoryManager, to perform inventory related operations into the ParamNetwork.

    InventoryManager addRecords/updateRecords/add/edit/get/getAll inventory from the ParamNetwork. Using NetworkManager can able to access this reference.

    IInventoryManager catalogueManager = networkManager.getInventoryManager();
    Want to perform any bulk upload items to implement this interface IBulkImport interface for remote files, for local files use FileBulkFileImportConfig. IInventoryManager defines below categories of operations:

    • addInventory method for add java catalogue object into ParamNetwork

    • editInventory method for edit java catalogue object into ParamNetwork

    • getInventory method for get catalogue object from ParamNetwork

    • incrementInventoryQtyByCatalogueID method for getting catalogueIDs from ParamNetwork

    • decrementInventoryQty method for getting catalogueIDs from ParamNetwork

    • decrementInventoryQtyByCatalogueID method for getting catalogueIDs from ParamNetwork

    Since:
    1.0
    Author:
    Jitendra Kumar Balla, ParamNetwork

      • addRecords

        public void addRecords(IBulkFileImportConfig uploadConfig)
                throws InvalidConfigException,
                       FileNotFoundException,
                       NetworkException,
                       AccessDeniedException
        Description copied from interface: IBulkImport
        Method import all the records from external file source to ParamNetwork.

        #addRecords(IBulkFileUploadConfig) <i>addRecords</i> method will read the file stream, then it will validate below items

        • Original file size with Steam bytes size
        • Validate file format with Param prescribed format
        • Record mandatory fields.
        If everything is valid, then it will add new record to param network, Otherwise it will throw an error.
        Specified by:
        addRecords in interface IBulkImport
        Parameters:
        uploadConfig - Upload config like, getFileContent(),File name,size, etc..,
        Throws:
        InvalidConfigException - If any file format is wrong then it will throw InvalidConfigException
        FileNotFoundException - Unable to read the content from the stream, then it will throw FileNotFoundException
        NetworkException - Unable to connect to ParamNode it will throw exception.
        AccessDeniedException - Not having enough access rights then it will throw an error
